

OOP Inheritance:  to build IS A relationship between the classes(parent/child, super/sub))

                   easiest way to get rich ====> extends

                   Child class(sub): can inherit all the variables and methods that are aaccessible and visible from the parent class

                   Parent class(super): can NOT inherit anything from child class. Constructor of parent class can never be inherited to the cchild class
                                       contains all the common features(variables/methods) of all child classes

                   Class A extends Class B


                   Advantages:

                   1. Avoid repitition, less code
                   2. improves the reusability of our codes
                   3. clean
                   4. less memory usage
                   5. easy to maintain